1934;;Whirlpool;;American;;Roy William Neill;;Jean Arthur, Jack Holt, Donald Cook;;drama, crime;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whirlpool_(1934_film);;Buck Rankin (Jack Holt) as a shady carnival promoter. He was jailed for a major crime just after learning that his wife is pregnant. Released after twenty five years behind bars, Rankin is anxious to make contact with his daughter Sandra (Jean Arthur), who knew nothing of his existence, since Rankin convinced the warden of the prison to send his wife a letter telling her that he was killed trying to escape.[1]